00:18:13.819 --> 00:18:16.920
such enormous harm on an enormous scale. So the

340
00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:21.000
misanthrop can acknowledge that certain failings are more intense

341
00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:23.400
in certain groups, and they can also acknowledge that

342
00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:26.599
certain failings are much worse in certain kinds of

343
00:18:26.599 --> 00:18:30.119
hostile social conditions. Maybe people do become more selfish

344
00:18:30.119 --> 00:18:33.589
and aggressive and violent under conditions of civil war.

345
00:18:33.959 --> 00:18:36.560
However, the misanthrope will also emphasize that the failings

346
00:18:36.560 --> 00:18:39.119
that they're interested in are not confined to awful

347
00:18:39.119 --> 00:18:42.829
people in awful circumstances. They are, as David Cooper

348
00:18:42.829 --> 00:18:46.030
says, entrenched and ubiquitous within the normal course of

349
00:18:46.030 --> 00:18:48.349
human life, but often in ways that people don't

350
00:18:48.349 --> 00:18:50.510
see. And I think one of the best examples

351
00:18:50.510 --> 00:18:52.469
of this is to look at the work on

352
00:18:52.469 --> 00:18:56.349
animal focused misanthropy. Now, if you look at the

353
00:18:56.349 --> 00:19:00.260
sorts of failings mentioned by the animal centered misanthropes,

354
00:19:00.589 --> 00:19:04.949
they emphasize that failings like greed, destructiveness, cruelty and

355
00:19:04.949 --> 00:19:10.469
brutality, these are. Typically located in institutions and practices

356
00:19:10.469 --> 00:19:14.229
like industrial animal agriculture, certain kinds of scientific and

357
00:19:14.229 --> 00:19:18.270
medical experimentation on animals, the the institutionalized ways we

358
00:19:18.270 --> 00:19:21.030
have of engaging with animals, that's where you locate

359
00:19:21.349 --> 00:19:24.469
these failings. So of course there are greedy individual

360
00:19:24.469 --> 00:19:27.069
people, people with the vice of greed, but greed

361
00:19:27.069 --> 00:19:30.229
should also be located within modern systems of industrial

362
00:19:30.229 --> 00:19:34.339
agriculture. And for that reason, the misanthrope says the

363
00:19:34.339 --> 00:19:37.760
failings are much more continuous features of human life

364
00:19:37.760 --> 00:19:40.359
than people think. But because they're located in systems

365
00:19:40.359 --> 00:19:43.500
that we don't often think critically about or systems

366
00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:46.500
that we are not informed about, we don't tend

367
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.219
to notice those failings. And you know, this is

368
00:19:49.219 --> 00:19:52.180
why for the misanthrope, it's very, very important that

369
00:19:52.180 --> 00:19:56.180
people should have a philosophical misanthropy that's based on

370
00:19:56.180 --> 00:19:58.739
investigation and research. For example, there's a huge amount

371
00:19:58.739 --> 00:20:02.010
of cruelty in industrial animal agriculture. But I take

372
00:20:02.010 --> 00:20:03.810
it the majority of people just don't know about

373
00:20:03.810 --> 00:20:07.130
it because those companies work hard to prevent you

374
00:20:07.130 --> 00:20:09.010
from finding out what they do. And of course

375
00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:12.089
most people don't really want to have detailed information

376
00:20:12.089 --> 00:20:14.849
about how animals are treated in factory farms because

377
00:20:14.849 --> 00:20:17.449
it's pretty terrible. Um, I mean recently I, I

378
00:20:17.449 --> 00:20:20.410
had a discussion with someone who insisted that animal

379
00:20:20.410 --> 00:20:23.859
agriculture in factories isn't cruel. And when I asked

380
00:20:23.859 --> 00:20:27.689
him what he thinks about practices like debeking, he

381
00:20:27.689 --> 00:20:30.290
quickly admitted he didn't know what that was, but.

382
00:20:31.180 --> 00:20:34.410
Debeaking is a primary example of a cruel practice.

383
00:20:34.660 --> 00:20:37.020
It is a practice which is premised upon cruel

384
00:20:37.020 --> 00:20:38.979
treatment of animals, but if you don't know about

385
00:20:38.979 --> 00:20:41.099
the practice, it's easy to think that it's less

386
00:20:41.099 --> 00:20:44.150
cruel than it is. And so for the misanthrope,

387
00:20:44.380 --> 00:20:47.060
these these vices and failings are much more distributed

388
00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:49.300
in the human world than people think. They're more

389
00:20:49.300 --> 00:20:52.459
common, more pervasive, and more entrenched. It's just that

390
00:20:52.459 --> 00:20:57.060
people have certain epistemic habits that turn their attention,

391
00:20:57.140 --> 00:20:58.579
their moral concern away from them.

392
00:20:59.839 --> 00:21:03.040
So, just to clarify this point, what is then

393
00:21:03.040 --> 00:21:08.650
the relationship between vices, corruption, and misanthropy?

394
00:21:10.229 --> 00:21:13.540
Well, 11 relation is that, uh, vices for the

395
00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:16.459
misanthrope are the terms of condemnation. So when they

396
00:21:16.459 --> 00:21:20.489
condemn humankind as awful, dreadful, or a moral disaster,

397
00:21:21.099 --> 00:21:23.939
what they're doing is arguing, um, to use David

398
00:21:23.939 --> 00:21:27.060
Cooper's terms, that a whole variety of vices and

399
00:21:27.060 --> 00:21:30.339
failings have come to be entrenched within the ways

400
00:21:30.339 --> 00:21:32.900
that we live, think and feel. So if you

401
00:21:32.900 --> 00:21:35.390
were to describe a range of human practices, structures,

402
00:21:35.540 --> 00:21:38.390
ambitions, and so on. You would have to use

403
00:21:38.390 --> 00:21:42.189
certain vices to describe them. Um, SO certain human

404
00:21:42.189 --> 00:21:45.630
ambitions are hubristic, certain ways of thinking about animals

405
00:21:45.630 --> 00:21:48.750
are, uh, insouciant. Many ways of treating animals are

406
00:21:48.750 --> 00:21:52.329
cruel and brutal. And for the misanthrope then vices

407
00:21:52.329 --> 00:21:54.890
are the terms of condemnation. What they are condemning

408
00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:57.969
are the vices and failings built into human forms

409
00:21:57.969 --> 00:22:01.689
of life. Now the connection to corruption is that

410
00:22:01.689 --> 00:22:05.329
for the misanthroppe, these vices and failings aren't just

411
00:22:05.329 --> 00:22:08.010
features of the system. They have a a sort

412
00:22:08.010 --> 00:22:11.369
of toxic or poisoning effect upon people, because if

413
00:22:11.369 --> 00:22:14.329
you are living and working within social systems that

414
00:22:14.329 --> 00:22:17.930
are contaminated with vices, one consequence can be that

415
00:22:17.930 --> 00:22:20.390
you yourself start to develop them. And that's the

416
00:22:20.390 --> 00:22:23.069
technical sense um of corrupting that I want to

417
00:22:23.069 --> 00:22:25.989
use. Something is corrupting if it tends to erode

418
00:22:25.989 --> 00:22:30.069
your moral excellences and feed your moral failings. For

419
00:22:30.069 --> 00:22:31.790
example, if you live within a system that is

420
00:22:31.790 --> 00:22:35.699
premised upon cruel and brutal treatment of animals, then

421
00:22:35.699 --> 00:22:38.790
that system will will persist if you yourself start

422
00:22:38.790 --> 00:22:41.500
to acquire those traits. So a system is corrupting

423
00:22:41.500 --> 00:22:45.109
when it's morally damaging, when living within that system

424
00:22:45.109 --> 00:22:47.469
is itself a source of moral damage and injury.

425
00:22:47.810 --> 00:22:49.400
And this is, this is a concept I'm taking

426
00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:52.680
from Claudia Card's work. And the connection then to

427
00:22:52.680 --> 00:22:55.560
misanthropy is for the misanthrope, the human world as

428
00:22:55.560 --> 00:22:58.839
we know it is both vicious and corrupt, but

429
00:22:58.839 --> 00:23:02.199
also corrupting, which is why misanthropes will describe the

430
00:23:02.199 --> 00:23:06.800
human world as poisonous, toxic, uh, dangerous. It's, it's

431
00:23:06.800 --> 00:23:09.959
polluted, as the Buddha says, the human world is

432
00:23:09.959 --> 00:23:13.959
burning, burning, burning with the fires of greed, hate,

433
00:23:13.969 --> 00:23:16.479
and delusion. And the function of these metaphors is

434
00:23:16.479 --> 00:23:19.880
to emphasize that. If you continue to live within

435
00:23:20.010 --> 00:23:23.849
a corrupting human world, you yourself will become corrupted

436
00:23:23.849 --> 00:23:27.319
and morally damaged, which is why for some misanthropes,

437
00:23:27.449 --> 00:23:30.609
the correct response to misanthropy is to withdraw from

438
00:23:30.609 --> 00:23:33.520
mainstream human life. And these are the misanthropes that

439
00:23:33.520 --> 00:23:37.969
can cause fugitives from mankind. These are the misanthropes

440
00:23:37.969 --> 00:23:41.020
whose whose dominant emotion is fear, fear at being

441
00:23:41.020 --> 00:23:44.030
corrupted. If they remain within a human world which

442
00:23:44.030 --> 00:23:47.150
is poisonous and toxic, and so these misanthropes respond

443
00:23:47.150 --> 00:23:50.270
by trying to withdraw from mainstream human life, maybe

444
00:23:50.270 --> 00:23:53.030
to isolated religious communities, or they live off the

445
00:23:53.030 --> 00:23:56.790
grid, or they try to separate themselves psychologically and

446
00:23:56.790 --> 00:24:00.540
physically from the mainstream human world. They become hermits.

447
00:24:00.869 --> 00:24:05.229
They live all alone. They withtreat and withdraw. Um,

448
00:24:05.349 --> 00:24:07.180
SO that there's a deep connection between, I think,

449
00:24:07.209 --> 00:24:10.430
vices, failings, corruption and misanthropy, because one of the

450
00:24:10.430 --> 00:24:12.829
questions a misanthrop has to answer is, well, if

451
00:24:12.829 --> 00:24:14.510
there are all these vices and failings, and they're

452
00:24:14.510 --> 00:24:17.910
so dreadful, why have they persisted? Um, WHY don't

453
00:24:17.910 --> 00:24:19.989
we do something about them? Why are they continuous

454
00:24:19.989 --> 00:24:22.790
features of human life? And one answer is that

455
00:24:22.790 --> 00:24:26.540
the human world has multiple systems of corruption which

456
00:24:26.540 --> 00:24:30.579
entrench, reinforce, protect, and conceal the failings of our

457
00:24:30.579 --> 00:24:30.979
world.

458
00:24:32.599 --> 00:24:35.500
So, yes, and later, I'm going to ask you

459
00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:39.099
more about the different kinds of attitudes that people

460
00:24:39.099 --> 00:24:42.420
can have toward misanthropy and also the different types

461
00:24:42.420 --> 00:24:47.969
of misanthropes out there. But do misanthropes include themselves

462
00:24:48.410 --> 00:24:50.699
among the rest of humanity? I know that you've

463
00:24:50.699 --> 00:24:53.810
already told us. Misanthropy is not really about passing

464
00:24:53.810 --> 00:24:57.839
judgment on specific individuals, but more on humanity as

465
00:24:57.839 --> 00:25:02.130
a whole and the systems, uh, humanity inhabits. But,

466
00:25:02.560 --> 00:25:06.750
uh, do they include themselves among the, the rest

467
00:25:06.750 --> 00:25:11.760
of humanity or do they position themselves as sort

468
00:25:11.760 --> 00:25:15.709
of morally superior to the rest of us?

469
00:25:17.449 --> 00:25:21.719
In my experience, most misanthropes will include themselves within

470
00:25:21.719 --> 00:25:24.560
the within the terms of condemnation. So one particular

471
00:25:24.560 --> 00:25:27.569
class of emotions that I think are very interesting

472
00:25:27.569 --> 00:25:31.369
and misanthropy are certain kind of self-directed emotions. So

473
00:25:31.369 --> 00:25:34.810
many misanthropes will feel guilt and shame and regret.

474
00:25:35.310 --> 00:25:38.069
As they come to recognize that their moral failings

475
00:25:38.069 --> 00:25:40.780
are continuous with the failings of the wider world,

476
00:25:41.219 --> 00:25:43.300
uh, for some misanthropists, it's a kind of shame,

477
00:25:43.630 --> 00:25:46.719
um, in coming to realize that your own failings,

478
00:25:46.729 --> 00:25:49.229
um, are so entrenched, that you yourself are part

479
00:25:49.229 --> 00:25:52.160
of a wider problem. So most misanthrops do include

480
00:25:52.160 --> 00:25:54.630
